The paper deals with the problem of graph reconstruction from noisy data using discrete Morse theory. The main focus is on the geometric properties of the reconstructed graph, which suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and data structures, which are typical topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves numerical analysis and optimization, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper involves the use of persistence-based methods, which are typical topics in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
